<p><strong>Prompt 17 — Renaissance Oil:</strong> "Portrait in the manner of Flemish Renaissance oil painting, single candlelight source from lower left creating chiaroscuro depth, rich jewel-tone clothing with fabric texture detail, museum-quality brushwork visible, Rembrandt self-portrait influence, timeless and majestic, deeply human"</p>

<h2>Complete Platform Guide: Adapting Prompts to Each AI Tool</h2>
<p>Each major AI image tool has distinct strengths and requires slightly different prompt strategies for best results.</p>
<p><strong>Midjourney v6 — Best Overall Realism:</strong> Append <code>--ar 1:1 --style raw --v 6</code> to all portrait prompts. The <code>--style raw</code> flag disables Midjourney''s automatic aesthetic enhancements and produces more neutral, photographic results that are easier to use as actual profile pictures. For facial consistency across multiple images, use <code>--cref [url]</code> with a reference photo. Control how closely facial features are matched using <code>--cw 50</code> (moderate) to <code>--cw 100</code> (strict). For maximum realism, add <code>--stylize 0</code>.</p>
<p><strong>DALL-E 3 via ChatGPT — Best Composition:</strong> DALL-E 3 excels at following complex compositional instructions. Frame prompts conversationally: "A professional portrait photograph of a person in their early 30s, shot with an 85mm lens at f/1.4, soft studio key light from the upper left..." Always add "photorealistic, professional photography, not illustration" to keep outputs photographic rather than painterly. DALL-E 3 handles "centered face, circle-crop safe composition" instructions very reliably.</p>
<p><strong>Stable Diffusion XL — Best Control, Free:</strong> Use Realistic Vision v6 or Juggernaut XL checkpoint. Negative prompt: "cartoon, anime, illustration, low quality, blurry, overexposed, double face, bad anatomy, plastic skin." Sampler: DPM++ 2M Karras. Steps: 30. CFG: 7. Resolution: 1024x1024. For personalized portraits, train a LoRA on 20-30 of your own photos and combine with a portrait checkpoint at 0.7 weight.</p>
<p><strong>Adobe Firefly — Best Commercial Safety:</strong> Use for business and client work where commercial licensing matters. Firefly is trained only on licensed content, making outputs safe for commercial use. Less flexible than Midjourney for specific styles, but more reliable for clean professional headshots.</p>

<h2>Instagram DP Technical Requirements You Cannot Ignore</h2>
<p>Technical mistakes at the generation stage result in profile pictures that look blurry, oddly cropped, or discolored after Instagram processes them. These specifications prevent every common technical problem.</p>
<p>Always generate at 1024x1024 minimum, ideally 2048x2048. Instagram''s upload compression reduces quality significantly, and starting with a higher-resolution source image results in a much crisper final display even after compression.</p>
<p>Instagram stores profile pictures internally at 320x320 pixels. The display sizes are: 110x110 in feed contexts, 150x150 on mobile profiles, and up to 300x300 on desktop. This means fine details — subtle textures, small background elements, intricate hair detail — are essentially invisible at display size. Focus your prompt energy on what reads clearly at 150 pixels: strong face shape, clear lighting contrast, readable expression.</p>
<p>Color space: Always ensure your generated image is in sRGB color space before uploading. Instagram converts everything to sRGB and applies JPEG compression. Images in P3 or ProPhoto color spaces will have colors shift during conversion. Most AI tools generate sRGB by default, but verify if you are post-processing in photo editing software.</p>
<p>The circle crop: Instagram crops your square image to a circle using a center-point crop. Anything in the corners is hidden. Keep your subject''''s face completely within a circle that represents approximately 85% of the image width. Leave at least 7-8% margin on all sides between the face edge and the frame edge.</p>

